[Common grazing ground is one of the risk factors for disease transmission.

A map of India can be seen at http://www.mapsofindia.com/images2/india-map.jpg, and Nagaland state, India can be seen at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4195346,314. - Mod.TTM]

[This event was initialy published by ProMED-mail as "undiagnosed," requesting information (20160418.4167911). In response, a brief report was gratefully obtained from one of EpiCore (ProMED-mail's Global Surveillance Project) participants in India. It indicated that the "Disease could be hemorrhagic septicaemia caused by _Pasteurella multocida_." Now, this diagnosis has been officially confirmed.

For background on HS, see the commentary in 20160425.4181247. - Mod.AS

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4195346,314.]
